title: Bug 121170: get column label from meta data object should return some user recognizable strings
OB: Currently, when the 'getcolumnlabel' function is called before data extraction, it does not return any user recognizable strings. Instead, it returns blank or non-descriptive values.
EB: Bug 121170: The 'getcolumnlabel' function should return user recognizable strings. It should provide the same labels before and after data extraction to ensure consistency.
SR:
1. Launch the software.
2. Access the meta data object.
3. Call the 'getcolumnlabel' function before performing any data extraction.
4. Check the returned value for each column label.
